    <ul style="overflow: hidden">

  

  

  

  

  

  </ul>
    <p>Hongxiang’s PhD studies user behavior in social virtual reality, and particularly how users leverage avatars to convey certain aspects of their identities.<br />
  <b>keywords:</b> Virtual Reality, Online Safety, HCI</p>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 clearfix">
    <p><img src="http://localhost:4000/mkhamis/images/teampic/bio-photo.png" class="img-responsive" width="25%" style="float: left" /></p>
    <h4>Yasmine Elfares</h4>
    <p><i>PhD Student, started Jan 2025<br />email: <a href="mailto:2956717E@student.gla.ac.uk">2956717E@student.gla.ac.uk</a> <br />page: &lt;&gt;</i></p>
    <ul style="overflow: hidden">

  

  

  

  

  

  </ul>
    <p>Yasmine’s PhD investigates the use of eye tracking in the context of software engineering, both for analyzing the behavior of software developers and also enable novel interaction techniques that leverage eye gaze.<br />
  <b>keywords:</b> Eye Tracking, Gaze Interaction, Software Engineering</p>
  </div>

